Russian Central Bank’s Deputy Chairman Resigns, Vedomosti Says

-- B y   Y u l i y a   F e d o r i n o v a
-- 
2011-08-04T04:10:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-04/russian-central-bank-s-deputy-chairman-resigns-vedomosti-says.html
Gennady Melikyan, the first deputy
chairman of  Russia ’s central bank, said he’s stepping down,
Vedomosti  reported  today.  Melikyan’s job includes monitoring the fiscal health of the
biggest banks, including Bank of Moscow, which is receiving a
record $14 billion bailout after state-run VTB Group agreed to
buy it.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Yuliya Fedorinova in Moscow at 
